        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): clear admin scopes for backend self-pairing",
        "body": "Summary\n- Stop treating shared token/password auth as sufficient to preserve self-declared operator scopes for local backend self-pairing.\n- Keep local approval-runtime scoped backend Gateway calls device-less when they carry `approvalRuntimeToken`.\n- Keep ordinary scoped local shared-token/password backend Gateway calls device-bound.\n- Add focused regression coverage for approval-runtime vs ordinary scoped shared-secret behavior.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior addressed:**\n- `callGatewayTool` approval-runtime loopback calls must remain device-less.\n- Ordinary scoped loopback shared-token backend calls must keep device identity.\n\n**Exact regression proof in this branch:**\n- `keeps loopback approval-runtime backend calls device-less`\n- `keeps loopback approval-runtime backend calls device-less even with shared token auth`\n- `keeps ordinary scoped shared-token backend calls device-bound`\n- `keeps remote approval-runtime backend calls device-bound`\n\nThese tests assert the client options directly (`deviceIdentity`, `approvalRuntimeToken`, `token`, and target URL), proving the current runtime behavior at the gateway call boundary.\n\n**Command run after this patch:**\n```text\npnpm vitest run src/gateway/call.test.ts src/agents/tools/gateway.test.ts\n```\n\n**Result:**\n```text\nTest Files  5 passed (5)\nTests  309 passed (309)\n```\n\nAdditional verification\n```text\ngit diff --check\n# no output\n```\n\nFixes openclaw/openclaw#72418\n",
